# Reference videos: don't commit the source files themselves.
# They're often someone else's copyrighted work, and they're large.
# We DO commit the _analysis/ output (frames + JSON + analysis.md) so the
# learnings travel with the repo.

*/source.*
*/source

# Track _analysis/ contents by default (frames, scene_cuts.json, metadata,
# analysis.md, etc.) — this un-ignores anything caught by parent rules.
!*/_analysis/
!*/_analysis/**

# Audio extracted during analysis (large WAV, regenerable). The exclusion
# MUST come AFTER the un-ignore above, otherwise it gets re-included.
# Use **/audio.16k.wav so it catches the file regardless of how deep the
# per-reference folder nests it (e.g. For\ RS/_analysis/<name>/audio.16k.wav).
**/audio.16k.wav
